title: Peterson’s wins propel Marywood

Peterson’s wins propel Marywood 
Kim Peterson won two individual events and helped lead 400 free relay team to a win, as Marywood University defeated Cazenovia College, 142-88, to pick its first victory of the season. 
Peterson won the 1000 freestyle in 12:11.16, which was 30 seconds better than the second-place finisher. She then won the 200 breastroke in 2:45.15 and helped the 400 free relay team win with a time of 4:04.02.
